Infectious salmon anaemia, Norway
---------------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 29 May 2013 from Dr Keren Bar-Yaacov, chief veterinary officer, Legislation, Norwegian Food Safety Authority, Brumunddal, Norway

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 28 May 2013
Date of pre-confirmation of the event: 28 May 2013
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: July 2010 [Troms]
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: infectious salmon anaemia [ISA] virus
Nature of diagnosis: suspicion, clinical, laboratory (advanced), necropsy
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country

New outbreaks (1)
Outbreak 1 (2013/3) 30117, Skjervoy, Nord Troms
Date of start of the outbreak: 28 May 2013
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Water type: salt water
Population type: farmed
Production system: semi-open
Affected animals: Atlantic salmon (_Salmo salar_)

Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Total animals affected
Species / Morbidity* / Mortality* / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Atlantic salmon / 3* / 3* / 1 224 100 / 100 000 / 50 000 / 138 500 / 0
* scale 0 to 5

Outbreak statistics [rates are "apparent" and expressed as percentages]
Species / morbidity rate / mortality rate / case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost**
Atlantic salmon (_Salmo salar_) / 8.17 / 4.08 / 50.00 / 15.40

**Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive

Epidemiological comments: The epidemiological survey has just started. The genotype of the ISA virus has not yet been identified. Associated with the epidemiological studies, the virus will be further characterized by the sequencing of segment 5 and 6 of the genome.

Control measures
Measures applied: movement control inside the country, emergency harvest, official destruction of clinically diseased aquatic animals, official disposal of carcasses, by-products and waste.
No vaccination
No treatment of affected animals

Measures to be applied: zoning, tracing forward, tracing back, surveillance outside containment and/or buffer zone, surveillance within containment and/or buffer zone

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type: Norwegian Veterinary Institute (National laboratory)
Species / Test / Test date / Result
Atlantic salmon / histopathology / 28 May 2013 / Positive
Atlantic salmon / immunohistochemical test / 28 May 2013 / Positive
Atlantic salmon / real-time PCR / 28 May 2013 / Positive

